Click on Create Load Balancer.
Choose Load Balancer Type:

Choose an Application Load Balancer.

Configure Load Balancer:

Name the load balancer (e.g., HelloWorldLB).
Scheme: Choose Internet-facing.
Listeners: Ensure you have a listener on HTTP (port 80).
Select your VPC and assign the subnets where you want to deploy the load balancer.
Configure Security Groups:

Choose a security group that allows inbound HTTP traffic (port 80).
Configure Target Group:

Choose a new target group (e.g., HelloWorldTG).
Target Type: Select Instance.
Protocol: HTTP, Port 80.
Health Checks: HTTP, Path /.
Register Targets:

Select your EC2 instance as the target for the load balancer.
Click Add to registered.
Create Load Balancer.
